<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="136" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,152,1151]" pageId="5" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,945,971]" pageId="5" pageNumber="136">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the grayish appearance of this species, from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1278,1359,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="136">griseus</emphasis>
(gray) plus the suffix 
<emphasis box="[318,391,982,1007]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="136">escens</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,661,1016,1044]" pageId="5" pageNumber="136" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,152,1151]" box="[199,661,1016,1044]" pageId="5" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1016,1043]" pageId="5" pageNumber="136">Distribution.</emphasis>
Palearctic 
<collectingCountry box="[477,541,1017,1043]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="136">Japan</collectingCountry>
(Honshu).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="136" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,152,1151]" pageId="5" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1053,1079]" pageId="5" pageNumber="136">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is characterized by its grayish head and thorax and male terminalia with apically curved cerci and narrow surstylus. The apically curved cerci are also found in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mesnil" authorityYear="1967" box="[961,1055,1090,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Blepharella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[961,1055,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="136">B. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the curve is much weaker in this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
